node.text:
“Perhaps most indelibly, Fanone offered his take on the rioters who’d heeded his pleas for mercy. “A lot of people have asked me my thoughts on the individuals in the crowd that helped me,” he drawled. “I think the conclusion I’ve come to is, like, thank you”—here he paused and squinted—“but f-ck you for being there.”

I posted the accompanying article from @time magazine, which is absolutely worth the read, on my Twitter @AGirlHasNoPres and in my stories.

node.text:
This guy is wonderful and it makes me sick to my stomach when he talks about the things that he saw that day. The worst possible people stormed the Capitol on January 6th. Privileged, entitled, and presumptuous that they were just going to walk in and no one would try to stop them.

Turns out every officer there wasn’t the kind of officer that would remove  barricades for them and unlock doors. They were enough of those, but I’m thankful this guy wasn’t one of them. But it sure sounds like they put them through hell.

node.text:
A, that woman is an absolute queen.

B, I wish someone would tell me to get back on my highway to hell, just once. I would fall over laughing right in front of them. That’s hilarious and the fact he’s about to have a coronary because they were short on baskets, is just beyond..

node.title: Get back on your highway to hell! 🤣
